## Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made

**Modified:**
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Vercel Analytics integration

### Implementation Details

1. **Package Installation**: The `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.6.1) was already installed in the project dependencies, so no additional installation was required.

2. **Analytics Integration**: 
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
   - Placed the `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout
   - The component is positioned after all other content providers and wrappers to ensure proper tracking

3. **Build Verification**: 
   - Successfully ran `pnpm install` to ensure all dependencies are available
   - Successfully ran `pnpm build` - the project compiles without errors
   - The build output shows all routes are properly configured and the Analytics component integrates seamlessly

### Technical Notes

- This is an App Router project (Next.js 15.4.10), so the Analytics component was added to `app/layout.tsx`
- The component is placed inside the `<body>` tag as recommended by Vercel's documentation
- No additional configuration is required - the Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals when deployed to Vercel
- The package manager used is `pnpm`, and the lockfile (`pnpm-lock.yaml`) was already up to date since the package was previously installed

### Testing

- ✅ Build completed successfully
- ✅ No TypeScript errors
- ✅ All routes compile correctly
- ✅ Analytics component properly integrated into the layout structure

The Analytics integration is now complete and ready for deployment. Once deployed to Vercel, the dashboard will automatically start collecting analytics data.
